Now, of course he has a right to change his name to whatever he desires, but surely you'd think he would at least consider other's feelings, right? He also told Saab to "Get Over" what Guest had done in the past, which is a little wrong considering he has no idea of the full ins and outs of what happened. Saab and Slee explained their side of the story and Slee apologized that he didn't handle the situation as well as he should've.

I then asked Void a few questions in DMs regarding the situation, and I was basically trying to find out if changed his name with motive to upset Saab or anything like that to which he responded no. I asked him if he knew about Guest, and he also responded no, which was where he lied to me because he clearly knew about Guest prior to changing his name as proved by a discussion in staff lounge on Friday. I then asked a few questions in different ways and he consistently stated he did not know of anyone with a similar name to him. I then confronted him for lying to me and he said he just didn't want to get in trouble. In response to your tweet along with many other complaints. I have decided to take down that tweet to avoid any confusions whatsoever. Of course, I do agree that there are improvements that I think is necessarily needed. Yes, we can voice our opinions about something else in everything. [03-Mar-20 07:51 PM] ethan;#0003
:bloxton3: **Reporting staff members working in unauthorized stations** :bloxton3: 

            Greetings members and guests of Bloxton Hotels! 

             It has come to the HR teams attention that an increase in the amount of staff members at Bloxton Hotels are being reported for working at a station they are unauthorized to work at. When reporting a staff member, you should be reminding them that they should not be working at that station without permission from an MR or higher. If there's no members from the MR Team around in the server, they cannot work at a station with a different position.
              The **INCORRECT** way to report a staff member who is not working at their authorized staton is if you ONLY take a picture of them standing and or working at that station, without you or another staff member asking them to please stop and return to their mandated station or the person is refusing to return to their mandated station. 
              The **CORRECT** way to report a staff member who is not working at their authorized station is to take three photos and or one video of the staff member working at the 
unauthorized station, of the staff being told to go back to their correct station, and of the staff refusing to go back to their mandated station. 
                **PLEASE NOTE** that you DO NOT report someone if they comply with you and go back to their designated station, you ONLY report if they REFUSE.


**Signed,**

*ethanx111*

*Bloxton Hotels | Shift Manager*

HINTING REPORTS

Greetings, everyone!

    Recently, there seems to have been a lot of confusion when it comes to people hinting. Hinting is not allowed yes, but it is NOT a major offence. If you hint, it doesnâ€™t mean you can never earn a promotion, it just means it may take longer. Now if it is someone continuously hinting, making it major hinting, thatâ€™s another story. Everyone has made mistakes in the past, so we donâ€™t want you feeling really stressed over hinting. 

If you see someone hinting, we ask that you collect the proper evidence and 
report them ASAP in hinting reports. Please donâ€™t keep the report and report the user a month later, because chances are nothing will be done. If you report a user that has earned a promotion with evidence of hinting from a month ago, that will not change their promotion. Hinting is not a demotable offence, as its not a major offence. This is why we ask that whenever you get a hinting report, report them right away. Reporting a user after they earned a promotion will not change their rank. If you have any questions or concerns please feel free to message any member of the HR team.

Sincerely,
staceyzn
General Manager
Bloxton Hotels

HINTING REPORTS

Greetings, everyone!

    Recently, there seems to have been a lot of confusion when it comes to people hinting. Hinting is not allowed yes, but it is NOT a major offence. If you hint, it doesnâ€™t mean you can never earn a promotion, it just means it may take longer. Now if it is someone continuously hinting, making it major hinting, thatâ€™s another story. Everyone has made mistakes in the past, so we donâ€™t want you feeling really stressed over hinting. 

    If you see someone hinting, we ask that you collect the proper evidence and report them ASAP in hinting reports. Please do not keep your report of the user hinting and then bring it to our attention a month later. What ends up happening is that there is no effect, meaning that nothing can be done. If you report a user that has earned a promotion with evidence of hinting from a month ago, that will not change their promotion. Hinting is not a demotable offence, as itâ€™s not a major offence. This is why we ask that whenever you get a hinting report, report them right away. Reporting a user after they earned a promotion will not change their rank. If you have any questions or concerns please feel free to message any member of the HR team.

Sincerely,
staceyzn
General Manager
Bloxton Hotels

[11-Mar-20 03:21 PM] Polk#1596
Hey, @High Rank. I want you guys to hear me out on this suggestion for the Senior Management checklist.

I really dislike the two "Attend Interview/Training Session" requirements on the Senior Management checklist. That is because I believe Senior Managements are mainly meant to host. (Which is true since they got promoted in order to be able to host + more.) Of course, I think they should be able to occasionally assist if needed. I just want their primary goal to be hosting. Sadly, those two requirements ruin that since we are pretty much forcing them to assist at least twice a week. At the time this was added to the checklist, I thought it was very reasonable and smart. However, after having it for a while, I kept getting fewer hosts for my sessions because a large amount of the Senior Managements keeps saying that **need** to assist instead of hosting since it is a requirement on their checklist. They are very right about that, therefore I can't really blame them for trying to get it done. After all, we can't force them to host. This is why I wish to replace those two requirements with "Host a session/assist" instead. So basically, two requirements will be "Host a session" as normal. However, the two other requirements will be "Host a session/assist." This will make it so Senior Managements can continue assisting while still getting two requirements checked off, but in cases when we need hosts, they will be able to host as well without any excuses. In my opinion, I believe it will greatly reduce the lack of hosts problem. (Other than hiring more active Seniors and getting rid of inactive ones) Furthermore, I believe the Senior Managements will like this option way better than the "must assist/cohost in a session" requirement. 

What do you guys think about this idea? I think this is worth discussing. Vote âœ… if you agree or âŒ if you do not agree. If you do not agree, please make sure to give a proper reason on why you do not agree. Thank you!

{Reactions}

[11-Mar-20 03:34 PM] Polk#1596
As I expected, we all have different ideas on how to fix this problem. Some people want to completely remove the assisting option, while others do not. Personally, I do not feel like making it prohibited to assist will solve the problem. We can still let them assist, but we just have to make some clear rules. For example, you are not allowed to co-host if a server is in need of a host. While co-hosting, you must not go AFK and supervise the stations along with the Managements. If the Seniors split the job of hosting, it will basically be the same amount of work a Management does if both ranks supervise. For normal assisting, we can say they may not assist if there's 3 managements in a server. Please vote âœ… if you want to let Seniors assist/co-host, but with some rules that must be followed at all times or vote âŒ if you think it is better to make it prohibited for Seniors to assist in any way. @High Rank

[11-Mar-20 04:16 PM] Polk#1596
We did not come to a final decision after our discussion, so I am going to ping ONCE more. (bonnie, if you talk about something not related to this topic you will be sent into timeout) Leaving out the co-hosting thing, we will vote about the assisting part on the Senior checklists. Basically, like I suggested before, I believe it is better to give them the option to assist on two of the requirements instead of making them host on all of them. This will allow them to be able to complete their checklists every week without having problems hosting due to not being quick enough to ask, not enough servers available, etc. Additionally, it will also remove the "I need to assist because I need to check it off on my checklist" problem which we keep on getting whenever we need hosts. We can for example have a rule to make them prioritize hosting as it is their primary job, like for example: seniors may not assist in another server if a server needs a host. So, once again, **leaving out cohosting, just talking about assisting** vote âœ… if you agree with my idea (better agree this time emma) or vote âŒ if you disagree. @High Rank

[11-Mar-20 05:44 PM] Polk#1596
Anything I should add to this announcement?


[11-Mar-20 05:44 PM] Polk#1596
Hi, everyone! I am going to announce a few changes to your checklists that will go live on Monday.

After a long discussion with the HR team, we have decided to change two of your requirements for your checklists. From now on, you will no longer be *required* to assist anymore. Those two requirements known as **"Attend Interview Session"** and **"Attend Training Session"** will now be changed into **"Host/Assist Interview Session"** and **"Host/Assist Training Session"**. 

This change was made to allow more servers to be hosted, while you guys still being able to complete your checklist every week without struggling to host. The reason why we replaced two of the hosting requirements to "Attend Interview/Training Session" in the first place was to help the people not being able to host 4 times every week. However, forcing you guys to assist created another problem for us. For example, some people would go: "Sorry, I can't host. I need to assist in order to complete my checklist this week." leaving some servers without a host. We could not really blame you for saying that since you probably just wanted to get it done. It is not like we can force any of you to host, as it is completely voluntary. (Except from the minimum requirements.) After all, the main task of a Senior Management is to host. Therefore, we want our Senior Managements to prioritize hosting instead of assisting. We find it unnecessary to have you guys assist in other servers when we need hosts. Additionally, we feel like most of you will prefer the option to assist rather than being forced to assist. Keep in mind that you guys will be allowed to assist, but that is only as long as there are no more than 3 managements in a server and if every server got a host.

If you have any questions about this change, feel free to ask me or any other HR. I suggest asking in #senior-lounge in case other people have the same question. Have a nice day!

[12-Mar-20 10:31 AM] xAfroTrey#9464
y'all


[12-Mar-20 10:31 AM] Polk#1596
Hi, everyone! I am going to announce a few changes to your checklists that will go live on Monday.

After a long discussion with the HR team, we have decided to change two of your requirements for your checklists. From now on, you will no longer be required to assist anymore. Those two requirements known as "Attend Interview Session" and "Attend Training Session" will now be changed into "Host/Assist Interview Session" and "Host/Assist Training Session". 

This change was made to allow more servers to be hosted, while you guys still being able to complete your checklist every week without struggling to host. The reason why we replaced two of the hosting requirements to "Attend Interview/Training Session" in the first place was to help the people not being able to host 4 times every week. However, forcing you guys to assist created another problem for us. For example, some people would go: "Sorry, I can't host. I need to assist in order to complete my checklist this week." leaving some servers without a host. We could not really blame you for saying that since you probably just wanted to get it done. It is not like we can force any of you to host, as it is completely voluntary. (Except from the minimum requirements.) After all, the main task of a Senior Management is to host. Therefore, we want our Senior Managements to prioritize hosting instead of assisting. We find it unnecessary to have you guys assist in other servers when we need hosts. Additionally, we feel like most of you will prefer the option to assist rather than being forced to assist. Keep in mind that you guys will be allowed to assist, but that is only as long as there are no more than 3 managements in a server and if every server got a host.

If you have any questions about this change, feel free to ask me or any other HR. I suggest asking in #senior-lounge in case other people have the same question. Have a nice day! @xM_inn

Greetings MR team!

I am here to present an ongoing issue that the HR team has been viewing over the past few months. We have noticed a majority of you are turning to certain MRs and having them present your own issues to us. This should not be tolerated. If you are responsible enough to carry an MR rank, you should be responsible enough to address your own issues and not having other people do it for you. Having other people talk to HRs about your own situations is adding in someone who should not be involved in the first place. If you have an issue that needs to be addressed to the HR team, whether it is a personal or group-wide issue, then you should present it by yourself. Thank you and have a nice day.

BmanPlays
Shift Manager
Bloxton Hotels

Greetings MR team!

       I am here to present an ongoing issue that the HR team has been viewing over the past few months. We have noticed a majority of you are turning to certain MRs and having them present your own issues to us. This should not be tolerated. If you are responsible enough to carry an MR rank, you should be responsible enough to address your own issues and not having other people do it for you. Carrying an MR rank means you are a role model for others, and shouldnâ€™t be having to make others talk about your concerns for you. Talking to friends about it may make you feel more comfortable, but that doesnâ€™t mean they should be addressing the issue to an HR for you. If it helps, you can address the issue with them, but donâ€™t make them do it all for you. Having other people talk to HRs about your own situations is adding in someone who should not be involved in the first place. 

       We understand some of you may feel uncomfortable messaging HRs, but you shouldnâ€™t ever feel that way as we are all a team here. If you have an issue messaging a certain HR, message a different HR.  Donâ€™t be afraid to approach us, as the issue may never get resolved if you never address it. If you have an issue that needs to be addressed to the HR team, whether it is a personal or group-wide issue, then you should present it by yourself. If you have any questions of concerns, please feel free to contact any member of the HR team. Thank you and have a nice day.

BmanPlays
Shift Manager
Bloxton Hotels

Greetings, Lanegorl.

This is a letter to inform you of your suspension here at Bloxton Hotels due to admin abuse, and acting unprofessional at the hotel. This suspension will last for a length of 3 days and will end approximately Sunday at 2:00 PM EST. When you are at the hotel, the bring command is only to be used when absolutely needed, such as if someone is stuck in a wall, or a troller has gotten away from security. It is not to bring people randomly whenever you wish. Another thing to consider at the hotel is professionalism. You set an example for other hotel guest and LRs, so when you act unprofessional such as encouraging trollers, abusing capitals, etc, that could encourage unprofessional behaviour from others. Please remember to act professional at all times while at the hotel and to not abuse the moderator commands you are given. We hope you learn from these mistakes over your suspension. If you have any questions or concerns, please feel free to message any member of the HR team.

Best Regards,
staceyzn
General Manager
Bloxton Hotels

**LEAKING POLICY UPDATE** ðŸ“ª 

Greetings, MR Team! Hope you all are having a great Saturday so far. Today, I would to provide to an update for you all on a topic that I'm sure you all have heard many times by now, Leaking. I'll be starting off with the CB list, since many users of the MR Team use it on a daily basis. I would like to remind you all that the document is for MR+ use only, so do not share it to members who are not apart of the MR Team. What could potentially happen if you send it to an LR is that they could possibly be the CBs themselves, or the document could end up spreading around with the CBs harassing the author itself, Bman. Also, I would like to point out the difference on a picture that's originally posted on the staff lounge or a user getting the picture from somewhere else and re-posting it to the staff lounge channel. Now, a picture that's originally posted on the stage lounge channel can be classified as leaking, and you will be met with some consequences depending on the review. On the other hand, re-posting a picture on staff lounge if you posted it somewhere else first is **NOT** leaking. As always, if you have a question regarding this announcement, be sure to to reach out with any member(s) of the HR Team whenever we're available. Thank you for reading, and have a good rest of your night!


Best Regards,

*xAfroTrey*

**Shift Manager**

**Bloxton Hotels**

**LEAKING POLICY UPDATE** ðŸ“ª 

Greetings, MR Team! Hope you all are having a great Saturday so far. Today, I would to provide to an update for you all on a topic that I'm sure you all have heard many times by now, Leaking. I'll be starting off with the CB list, since many users of the MR Team use it on a daily basis. I would like to remind you all that the document is for MR+ use only, so do not share it to members who are not apart of the MR Team. What could potentially happen if you send it to an LR is that they could possibly be the CBs themselves, or the document could end up spreading around with the CBs harassing the author itself, Bman. Also, I would like to point out the difference on a picture that's originally posted on the staff lounge or a user getting the picture from somewhere else and re-posting it to the staff lounge channel. Now, a picture that's originally posted on the stage lounge channel can be classified as leaking, and you will be met with some consequences depending on the review. On the other hand, re-posting a picture on staff lounge if you posted it somewhere else first is **NOT** leaking. As always, if you have a question regarding this announcement, be sure to to reach out with any member(s) of the HR Team whenever we're available. Thank you for reading, and have a good rest of your night!


Best Regards,

*xAfroTrey*

**Shift Manager**

**Bloxton Hotels**
